main event: A military pilot reported visual observation and radar tracking of unknown objects while airborne on November 8, 1967, approximately 71 miles west of Omaha, Nebraska.
interesting points: The pilot reported the objects changed color from reddish-orange to yellow to white.
Radar tracked six to eight objects within a range of 1.5 to 5 miles.
The Chicago Center initially identified the objects as normal aircraft, but later could not provide any details about the observation.
The original film record and observational data from the incident were reportedly destroyed.
Attempts to obtain further information about the incident from various Air Force sources were unsuccessful.
sighted object: Unidentified luminous objects detected visually and on radar
